sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant U as User
    participant C as Claude (Skill)
    participant AQ as AskUserQuestion
    participant FS as File System
    participant REG as MCP Registry
    participant VAL as Validator

    Note over U,C: Phase 1 — Discovery
    U->>C: "I want to create a plugin"
    C->>AQ: What problem does this plugin solve?
    AQ-->>C: "Automate our release process"
    C->>AQ: Who are the primary users?
    AQ-->>C: "Engineering team"
    C->>AQ: What external tools does it need?
    AQ-->>C: "GitHub, Slack, PagerDuty"

    Note over C: Phase 2 — Component Planning
    C->>C: Analyze requirements →<br/>Determine needed primitives
    C->>AQ: Confirm component plan:<br/>☑ 3 Skills ☑ MCP ☐ Agents ☐ Hooks
    AQ-->>C: Confirmed ✓

    Note over C,AQ: Phase 3 — Design & Clarify
    loop For each skill
        C->>AQ: Skill name, trigger phrases,<br/>arguments, required tools?
        AQ-->>C: Skill specification details
    end
    C->>AQ: MCP servers: GitHub, Slack, PagerDuty?<br/>Auth type? Required scopes?
    AQ-->>C: Confirmed integrations

    Note over C,FS: Phase 4 — Implementation
    C->>FS: Create plugin directory structure
    C->>FS: Write .claude-plugin/plugin.json<br/>(name, version, description, author)

    loop For each component
        C->>FS: Create skills/skill-name/SKILL.md<br/>(frontmatter + imperative body)
        C->>FS: Create skills/skill-name/references/<br/>(detailed supplementary docs)
    end

    C->>FS: Write .mcp.json<br/>(HTTP endpoints for GitHub, Slack, PagerDuty)
    C->>FS: Write CONNECTORS.md<br/>(~~source control → GitHub, ~~chat → Slack)
    C->>FS: Write README.md (user docs)

    Note over C,VAL: Phase 5 — Review & Package
    C->>VAL: claude plugin validate path
    VAL-->>C: Validation passed ✓
    C->>FS: Package → release-manager.plugin
    C-->>U: Plugin ready for installation<br/>[Rich preview + Accept button]
